com.hexoskin.hsapi_android

Interface HexoskinDataListener


  • public interface HexoskinDataListener
    Implements this interface to receive biometric data from the Hexoskin Device. Here is how it works : when you receive data from the Hexoskin Device via your input stream of the bluetooth socket, you then send those bytes to the HexoskinAPI via the decode method and the HexoskinAPI will then notify the HexoskinDataListener of the decoded data.

      • onRawData

        void onRawData(HexoskinDataType type,
               long time,
               int[][] values)
        Gets called when HexoskinAPI decode a raw level data such as ECG, PPG, etc
        Parameters:
        type - HexoskinDataType type of raw level data
        time - hexotimestamp
        values - the values, x = channels, y = values. In the case of respiration, you will receive 2 channels and 8 values by channels, one for thorasic and one for abdominal. For Acceleration, you will have 3 channels (x,y,z) and 8 values per channels.
